Abstract = {Nuclear Forensics is a rapidly evolving field with a steadily increasing
   number of publications. Research in developing or consolidating
   signatures and methods in various analytical areas, such as elemental
   and isotopic parameters, age dating and morphology have resulted in
   significant progress. Moreover, the development of new reference
   materials for uranium ore concentrate, the application of
   micro-analytical techniques and the increasing use of data evaluation
   techniques such as machine learning or deep learning further add to the
   nuclear forensic toolbox. The examination of samples from real incidents
   demonstrate the usefulness and the investigative value of nuclear
   forensic techniques. (C) 2021 The Author(s). Published by Elsevier B.V.},
