   Chengdu, PEOPLES R CHINA, DEC 16-19, 2022},
Abstract = {As China's smart judicial field has been continuously improved and the
   technologies in Deep Learning has been research hotspots, methods in
   Text Classification are more and more frequently used in legal judgment
   documents. As the carrier of the final legal judgment, the judgment
   document contains a lot of valuable information, including the
   description of the facts, the legal terms on which the judgment is
   based, the type of crime, and the name of the case. At present, the
   classification methods of judgment documents on criminal offenses and
   legal provisions mainly focus on machine learning and model fusion, but
   due to the excessive number of labels, it is easy to lead to extremely
   unbalanced distribution of sample categories. Therefore, this paper
   improves the focal loss by adding label prior knowledge, and solves the
   imbalance problem based on the RTR-SA model. Experimental results on the
   CAIL2018-Small dataset show that the proposed method outperforms
   existing methods.},
