Month = {JAN-MAR},
Abstract = {Phishing was introduced in 1996, and now phishing is the biggest
   cybercrime challenge. Phishing is an abstract way to deceive users over
   the internet. Purpose of phishers is to extract the sensitive
   information of the user. Researchers have been working on solutions of
   phishing problem, but the parallel evolution of cybercrime techniques
   have made it a tough nut to crack. Recently, machine learning-based
   solutions are widely adopted to tackle the menace of phishing. This
   survey paper studies various feature selection method and dimensionality
   reduction methods and sees how they perform with machine learning-based
   classifier. The selection of features is vital for developing a good
   performance machine learning model. This work is comparing three broad
   categories of feature selection methods, namely filter, wrapper, and
   embedded feature selection methods, to reduce the dimensionality of
   data. The effectiveness of these methods has been assessed on several
   machine learning classifiers using k-fold cross-validation score,
   accuracy, precision, recall, and time.},
