   Acad Sci, Syst Res Inst; IEEE Computat Intelligence Soc Poland Sect;
   Poornima Coll Engn; Univ Teknologi MARA Kedah Branch, Fac Comp \& Math
   Sci; IEEE IE IA Malaysia Joint Chapter; IEEE Poland Sect; IEEE Comp Soc;
   IEEE Computat Intelligence Soc; IEEE Comp Soc Poland Sect Chapter},
Abstract = {Recently, crime cases have been highly reported due to the increased of
   the utilization of technology. The development of system aims to
   identify the probable suspects based on social network messages. The
   study focuses on certain features extracted from the content of social
   media text messages. There were four features identified namely
   location, time, object and person. These four features help to manage
   the system based on specified crime messages. The implementation of
   features for crime suspect profiling (CSP) utilizes text mining through
   named entity recognition to identify the word or phrase for particular
   features. In this study, the suspect measure was obtained through the
   integrated similarity. Results obtained from the experiments conducted
   have revealed the similarity value that reflects the possibility of a
   contact as a suspect to the crime. The results of this study affirmed
   that the suspect profiling through the messages content is promising to
   identify the suspects.},
